Member of <a href="http://www.eqdragoncouncil.org">Dragon Council</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/12/01 11:05:39 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> too many weapons</span><hr size=1> At L25 you sure do carry around an arsenal of weapons. I know it is a good idea to max out all of your weapon skills. but I would suggest getting them now maxed at L25 and then selling off your nathsar and silver etched warhammer at the least. The centi war spear is by far the better option of your weapon choices currently.<br>
<br>
That should get you 1-2kpp I suppose which will definitely allow you to upgrade your gear. You can then easily upgrade to fineplate in some areas or better dropped stuff.<br>
Some cheap items that are reasonable upgrades.<br>
bracers - bracer of scavenging 9ac 5dex/sta - probably around 2-300pp<br>
neck - fine plate or look around for a rygorr one. you can sometimes find those for 2-300pp now. 9ac +stats.           <br>
shoulder - tattered mantle, crested spaulders or adamanite epolets are all reasonably cheap and good upgrades. None of these should set you back more than 300pp. <br>
<br>
If you just upgraded these 3 slots from selling off your old weapons you'll gain 30ac and all of the stats in the place of your current 7 ac 7int/7str combined stats. And it should run you a total of 1kpp. Not a bad upgrade if you ask me. heh.<br>
<br>
A personal preference I'd consider selling the helm of ro and picking up a skull shaped barbute. same ac but 35 hp 10 vs magic as opposed to the 7 wis. and the ssb is dirt cheap. you can find em for like 75pp these days.<br>
<br>
These are just some suggestions. Currently you are doing quite well. I didn't get my first piece of ro until I was L30 I think. I was using a combine longsword at L24. lol. Anway your gear should do you fine, but you may want to consider some of my suggestions.<br>
<br>
Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ulittleman300.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Littleman300</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/12/01 11:31:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> level 25?</span><hr size=1> A geez...Did i forget to mention that I started a new paladin..He's not level 25...but level 1 =)<br>
<br>
I have those weaps not to sell but to keep the stats maxxed. Only reason I keep the 2hb and nathsar. Can anyone recommend a cheap 1hb that i can use to max that skill while still doing decent damage? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utelumehtar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telumehtar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(12/12/01 12:42:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level 25?</span><hr size=1> for a cheap 1hb that is VERY nice look at either the Blackjack 7dmg/21del or a Mudman Enforcer 8dmg/20del.<br>
<br>
Blackjacks go for around 50 to 200pp average and the Mudman about 500 to 750pp average.<br>
<br>
For 1hs a Ghoulbane would actually be better than what you are wielding currently.  A Yakesha is also a better choice and I have seen those selling for under 1K easy sometimes as low as 500pp.<br>
<br>
The Nathsar I would actually hold onto (if you can get cash some other way) til about level 35 or so.  The speed on that sword makes it an incredible weapon in the early stages of the game.<br>
<br>
The Silver Etched Warhammer is also nice due to its solid damage potential but also decent speed.<br>
<br>
Both weapons make excellent training weapons.   The Centi spear is at the moment your best damage weapon for sure.<br>
<br>
Anyhow good luck and I'll warn you now that paladins can be rough for the first half of the game but once they hit 30 and start getting better healing abilities over the other Hybrids is when we start to shine. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=13319.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showMessage?topicID=13394.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=13385.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.threadControl?topicID=13385.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=13385.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=13385.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="paladinsofnorrathgeneral">General<option value="paladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests">Holy Swords and Quests<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm8">Epic Quests<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm9">Paladin Polls<option value="paladinsofnorrathtomeso